==English==
===Etymology===
From {{Arab.}} {{ARchar|ذنب الدجاجة}} (''dhanab ad-dajājah'') ‘hen's tail’, from {{ARchar|[[ذنب]]}} ‘tail’ + {{ARchar|[[دجاجة]]}} ‘hen’.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Deneb'''

#{{star}}: A [[blue giant]] [[star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Cygnus]]; Alpha (α) Cygni. It is one of the brightest stars in the night sky, and one of the most [[luminous]] stars known.

